        },
        {
          "username": "Jason Hocker",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "107426426143781631003",
          "user_review_count": 3,
          "user_photo_count": 0,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjVyNs4wXckMJAx_CK0jbSmC955rbQjb7haKoUFGrKEbc94kEaMy=s120-c-rp-mo-br100",
          "description": "This review is for the office of Dr Lev Haimoff. Had my first visit to find a new PCP.  Happy to say, my search has ended.  He spent about an hour with me for my intake.  I never felt rushed.  I got the impression that he is a great doctor (I\u2019m an RN at a local hospital, so I work with a lot of them). I thought the office was presentable and clean. Some previous reviews mentioned conflict with his office staff. That was not my experience. They were polite, professional, and did not make me wait. If you find yourself at odds with your doctor\u2019s office, here are some helpful tips\u2026 Be on time. If you don\u2019t show up, expect to pay a small fee. If you don\u2019t receive a pre-appointment confirmation, try calling the morning of. Be patient, and understand that they are the ones in demand, not you. Be extra patient if it\u2019s a sick visit because they are squeezing you into an already busy schedule. Thoughtfully consider whether your issue is one for your PCP, urgent care or emergency room. It\u2019s really difficult to find a good, readily available PCP these days, and I\u2019m so happy to have found one in Dr Haimoff.",
          "link": "https://www.google.com/maps/reviews/data=!4m8!14m7!1m6!2m5!1sChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSUN6Z1BIMlJnEAE!2m1!1s0x0:0x23ef228ade84cb30!3m1!1s2@1:CIHM0ogKEICAgICzgPH2Rg%7C%7C?hl=en",
          "date": "2 years ago",
          "date_iso8601": "2024-05-29T16:50:44+00:00"
        },
        {
          "username": "Joshua Desjardins",
          "rating": 5,
          "contributor_id": "107186054649842505100",
          "user_review_count": 14,
          "user_photo_count": 2,
          "user_thumbnail": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/a-/ALV-UjUzYXgnK3BrsCFO1U6hCXOuTwtLcQw6zEIxS4gUC0geDpEVjO1f=s120-c-rp-mo-ba12-br100",
          "description": "Dr. Haimoff\u2019s bedside manner is extremely respectable and I\u2019ve never felt more comfortable around a doctor. I feel like I can confide in him with my personal needs, concerns and questions. I refuse to change doctors until he retires, which hopefully won\u2019t be anytime soon.",
